Tibet: Cry of the Snow Lion;;90;;86;;NC;;This documentary by director Tom Peosay presents the history of Tibet under Chinese occupation. While the film depicts life at Buddhist monasteries that are closely associated with the mountainous region, it also shows other sides of the country, capturing the poverty found in the city of Lhasa, as well as sweeping shots of the expansive Tibetan wilderness. Many notable actors contribute their voices to the production, including Martin Sheen, Ed Harris and Susan Sarandon.;;Documentary;;Tom Peosay;;2003;;Edward Edwards,Ed Harris,Shirley Knight,Tim Robbins,Susan Sarandon,Martin Sheen;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/tibet_cry_of_the_snow_lion